# memory/

Your personal memory files live here — they are gitignored on purpose.

On first install, copy the generic templates into place:

    bash scripts/init-templates.sh

Or run `npm install` — the postinstall hook does it automatically
if `memory/SOUL.md` is missing.

Edit any of the copied files to teach your agent who you are, what it can do,
and what you care about. The agent reads them at every boot.

Templates live in `memory/templates/` (committed) — the copies in `memory/`
(SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, ...) are yours and stay private.
